                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s5"><span class="num">05</span> Subscription cancellation</h3>
                    <h4>5.1 How to cancel</h4>
                    <p>You can cancel your subscription at any time through:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Account Settings &rarr; Subscription &rarr; Cancel Subscription</li>
                        <li>Contacting support at <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a></li>
                        <li>Calling {{ support_phone }}</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>5.2 Cancellation effect</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period</li>
                        <li>You retain access until the paid period expires</li>
                        <li>No refund for the remaining days in the current billing period</li>
                        <li>Automatic renewal is disabled</li>
                        <li>You have 30 days to export your data after cancellation</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>5.3 Reactivation</h4>
                    <p>You can reactivate your account within 90 days of cancellation. After 90 days, your data will be permanently deleted.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s6"><span class="num">06</span> Refund request process</h3>
                    <h4>6.1 How to request a refund</h4>
                    <p>To request a refund, follow these steps:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Email <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a> with subject &ldquo;Refund Request&rdquo;</li>
                        <li>Include your account details (Company ID, Admin ID, registered email)</li>
                        <li>Provide reason for refund request</li>
                        <li>Include transaction ID or payment receipt</li>
                        <li>Specify preferred refund method</li>
                    </ol>
                    <h4>6.2 Refund processing time</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Review period:</strong> 2-3 business days to review your request</li>
                        <li><strong>Approval notification:</strong> Email confirmation if approved</li>
                        <li><strong>Processing time:</strong> 5-7 business days for refund to be processed</li>
                        <li><strong>Bank credit:</strong> Additional 5-10 business days depending on your bank</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>6.3 Refund methods</h4>
                    <p>Refunds are issued to the original payment method:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Credit/Debit Card:</strong> Refunded to the same card</li>
                        <li><strong>UPI:</strong> Refunded to the same UPI ID</li>
                        <li><strong>Net Banking:</strong> Refunded to the same bank account</li>
                        <li><strong>Wallet:</strong> Refunded to the same wallet</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s7"><span class="num">07</span> Upgrade and downgrade policy</h3>
                    <h4>7.1 Upgrading your plan</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Upgrades take effect immediately</li>
                        <li>You are charged the prorated difference for the remaining billing period</li>
                        <li>New customer limits apply immediately</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>7.2 Downgrading your plan</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Downgrades take effect at the next billing cycle</li>
                        <li>No refund for the difference in the current billing period</li>
                        <li>You must reduce customers to fit the new plan limit before downgrade</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s8"><span class="num">08</span> Chargebacks and disputes</h3>
                    <h4>8.1 Chargeback policy</h4>
                    <p>If you initiate a chargeback with your bank without first contacting us:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your account will be immediately suspended</li>
                        <li>We will provide transaction evidence to your bank</li>
                        <li>Chargeback fees may be charged to your account</li>
                        <li>Account reactivation requires payment of outstanding amounts plus chargeback fees</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>8.2 Dispute resolution</h4>
                    <p>Before initiating a chargeback, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a>. We are committed to resolving billing disputes fairly and promptly.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s9"><span class="num">09</span> Special circumstances</h3>
                    <h4>9.1 Technical issues</h4>
                    <p>If you experience technical issues preventing platform use:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Contact support immediately at {{ support_phone }}</li>
                        <li>We will work to resolve the issue within 24-48 hours</li>
                        <li>If unresolved, you may be eligible for a prorated refund</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>9.2 Force majeure</h4>
                    <p>Refunds are not provided for service interruptions caused by events beyond our control (natural disasters, government actions, internet outages, etc.).</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s10"><span class="num">10</span> Annual subscription refunds</h3>
                    <p>Annual subscriptions receive a discount compared to monthly billing. Refund terms for annual subscriptions:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Within 30 days:</strong> Full refund under money-back guarantee</li>
                        <li><strong>After 30 days:</strong> No refunds for annual subscriptions</li>
                        <li><strong>Cancellation:</strong> Access continues until the annual period ends</li>
                        <li><strong>No prorating:</strong> No prorated refunds for unused months</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s11"><span class="num">11</span> Add-on services</h3>
                    <p>Refunds for add-on services (additional SMS credits, WhatsApp credits, etc.):</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Unused credits are non-refundable</li>
                        <li>Credits remain valid for 12 months from purchase</li>
                        <li>Credits are transferable if you upgrade plans</li>
                        <li>Credits are forfeited upon account closure</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s12"><span class="num">12</span> Exceptions and special cases</h3>
                    <p>We may consider refund requests outside this policy on a case-by-case basis for exceptional circumstances. Contact us at <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a> to discuss your situation.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s13"><span class="num">13</span> Policy changes</h3>
                    <p>We reserve the right to modify this Refund &amp; Return Policy at any time. Changes will be communicated via:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Email notification to registered users</li>
                        <li>Prominent notice on the platform</li>
                        <li>Updated policy page with revision date</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Changes do not apply retroactively to subscriptions purchased before the change.</p>
                </div>

